last_episode_to_air.name: The Reason
last_episode_to_air.overview: Lady Parts are thwarted as the record label begins to interfere with their music. As the band reach breaking point, can they reclaim their voice and the greater sisterhood?

name: We Are Lady Parts
overview: An anarchic, laugh-out-loud music comedy following a Muslim female punk band called Lady Parts, tracking the highs and lows of the band members as seen through the eyes of Amina Hussein — a geeky doctorate student who is recruited to be their unlikely lead guitarist.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: Series two sees the band return with a renewed artistic mission after the high of their first UK tour, only to find a rival band threatening their delicate status quo. But as the reality of chasing success sets in, Lady Parts embarks on recording their first album, juggling personal ambitions and questioning whether 'making it big' is really what they want…

episodes.name: Play Something
episodes.overview: Two worlds collide when Lady Parts, who need a lead guitarist, set their sights on Amina, who just wants to find a husband.

episodes.name: Potential Future Spouse
episodes.overview: Lady Parts make Amina an enticing offer: audition with them and they'll set her up with Ayesha's hot brother, Ahsan

episodes.name: Earth Natives
episodes.overview: Amina's secret double life starts to take its toll when Lady Parts' big audition falls on the same day as her best friend Noor's engagement party

episodes.name: Godzilla
episodes.overview: Unable to get a gig and at a low ebb, Lady Parts return to their humdrum lives. Will they ever get the break they need?

episodes.name: Represent
episodes.overview: The band are buzzing about being interviewed by influencer Zarina. But they soon find themselves pushed to breaking point. Lady Parts are famous, but at what cost?

episodes.name: Sparta
episodes.overview: Amina's at an all-time low: publicly shamed, shunned by her uni friends, and out of Lady Parts. But Momtaz is hell-bent on getting the band back together...

episodes.name: Villain Era
episodes.overview: Saira announces it's time for Lady Parts to record their debut album. Amina explores her 'villain era', a new attitude of being a bad mother with boundaries and non-negotiables. And a rival Muslim band, Second Wife, threatens the band's status quo.

episodes.name: Malala Made Me Do It
episodes.overview: After being upstaged by Second Wife at Transcience Fest, things go from bad to worse: a shock eviction leaves the band without a rehearsal space. But a chance lifeline leads them down an unexpected path.

episodes.name: It's Britney B****
episodes.overview: For the first time, the band are mercenaries, hired guns... wedding singers. After tearing the roof off 'Uncle' Steve's wedding with a banging Britney cover, Saira is approached by Clarice, a top music manager who has her eye on Lady Parts.

episodes.name: Don't Let Me Be Misunderstood
episodes.overview: Still reeling from the disastrous photoshoot, the band are adrift, on a break, leaving each of them to explore their own personal crossroads.

episodes.name: Funny Muslim Song
episodes.overview: Lady Parts finally record their dream album at the legendary Molico Studios, while a heartbroken Momtaz goes on an odyssey of her own. But Saira's attempt at writing a political song tests boundaries.

episodes.name: The Reason
episodes.overview: Lady Parts are thwarted as the record label begins to interfere with their music. As the band reach breaking point, can they reclaim their voice and the greater sisterhood?
